INSERT INTO `how_works` (`id`, `description`, `image`, `status`, `created_by`, `updated_by`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(1, '<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\">Project Management Life Cycle</h4>\r\n<p>The Project Management Life Cycle is a set of tasks that must be completed in order for the project&#39;s objectives or targets to be met. It is a framework that incorporates the processes involved in turning a concept into a reality. The Project Management Lifecycle process is separated into four major phases: Initiation, Planning, Execution, and Monitoring, Controlling, and Closing.</p>\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/uploads/images/plc-tmc.png\" style=\"width: 95%; height: 95%;\" /></h4>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>The initiation phase specifies the steps necessary to begin a new project. The project beginning phase&#39;s goal is to determine what the project should accomplish.</li>\r\n	<li>The planning phase accounts for roughly half of the entire process. The planning phase specifies the scope of the project as well as the project&#39;s aim. It starts with the results of the beginning phase (charter, preliminary scope statement, and project manager). The planning phase&#39;s output is used as input for the execution phase.</li>\r\n	<li>The executing phase includes all of the actions outlined in the project management plan. This process entails managing stakeholder expectations, collaborating with people and resources, and carrying out other project-related operations.</li>\r\n	<li>Following the execution phase, the monitoring and controlling phase is activated to ensure that the project is on track. Various adjustments and evaluations are carried out during this phase in order to improve the project&#39;s performance.</li>\r\n</ol>', '202202120506data-home-icon1.png', 1, 1, 2, '2022-02-11 23:06:13', '2022-02-19 12:08:10'),
(2, '<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\">Development Methodology</h4>\r\n<p>Agile Scrum Methodlogy is a simple, iterative, and incremental approach for creating, delivering, and maintaining complex products. The framework challenges the traditional, sequential approach to product development and enables teams to self-organize by promoting physical co-location or close online cooperation of all team members, as well as daily face-to-face communication among all team members and disciplines involved.</p>\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/uploads/images/dev-tmc.png\" style=\"width: 70%; height: 70%;\" /></h4>\r\n<p>A crucial scrum concept is the knowledge that customers will modify the scope of what is desired (commonly referred to as requirements volatility) and that there may be unexpected obstacles &ndash; for which a predictive or planned approach is unsuitable. These changes come from a multitude of sources, but understanding why is immaterial, according to scrum, and change should simply be accepted, embraced, and studied for advantages.</p>\r\n<p>As a result, scrum takes an empirical approach based on evidence, accepting that the problem cannot be fully understood or defined at the outset and instead focusing on how to maximize the team&#39;s ability to deliver quickly, respond to emerging requirements, and adapt to evolving technologies and changes in market conditions.</p>', '202202120507data-home-icon2.png', 1, 1, 2, '2022-02-11 23:07:14', '2022-02-19 12:24:42'),
(3, '<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\">Quality Assurance Process</h4>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/uploads/images/qms-tmc.png\" style=\"width: 396px; height: 336px;\" /></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>To increase the regularity of releases and minimize faults, we implemented DevOps for quality assurance. It is an approach that promotes quick, brief, iterative application development and deployment. The concept of QA in Dev Operations is critical as a method for continual improvement. This is done throughout the development and deployment of a feature. Quality Assurance is an essential component of both the development and testing processes in Dev Operations. Dev Operations monitors the entire process from start to finish. Previously, quality was compromised during the manufacturing process.</p>', '202202121105data-home-icon1.png', 1, 1, 2, '2022-02-12 05:05:59', '2022-02-16 17:09:03');

