(4, 'Annual reports', 'বার্ষিক প্রতিবেদন', '<h3><strong>Annual report &nbsp;<br />\r\nCampaign &ldquo;Equality through Dignity&rdquo;&nbsp;<br />\r\nReporting period: July 2017-June 2018&nbsp;</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Introduction:&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\nThe overarching goal of the &ldquo;Equality through Dignity&rdquo; campaign is to enhance women&rsquo;s private and public&nbsp;status through shifting societal mind-sets and attitude towards women to a positive perception about&nbsp;&nbsp;them to ultimately reduce discrimination and violence against women. The hypothesis is if women are&nbsp;&nbsp;respected and honoured then there will be less violence against them. To do this, the major focus is on&nbsp;&nbsp;raising mass awareness regarding the largely invisible contribution of women&rsquo;s paid and unpaid care work&nbsp;to the family, society and &nbsp;state, and to see this reflected not only in changing social norms, but in policy&nbsp;&nbsp;such as in the procedures for estimating national GDP. &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Simultaneously, the campaign aims to highlig work has on domestic violence, poverty and seeks to reshape social expectations and nor of unpaid care work within the household. The &quot;World Rural Women&#39;s Day&quot; is being observed to highlight the role played by rural women&nbsp;in food production and food security by &nbsp;7 MJF-Partners at 8 unions under Shatkhira, Jhinaidha,Kurigram, Bandarbon, Rajshahi, Shirajgonj and Manikgonj districts. Main objectives to highlight&nbsp;the &nbsp;critical role and contribution of rural women, including indigenous women, in enhancing&nbsp;agricultural and rural development, improving food security and eradicating rural poverty, which&nbsp;needs to recognize socially and economically.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Few Highlights:&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n<strong>Grassroots Activation:&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;<br />\r\n800 women agriculture workers gathered in a place at Gorpara Union Parishad, District Manikgonj on 23r October, 2017 to highlight the importance of rural women&rsquo;s agricultural role and responsibilities which i totally un-recognized. &nbsp;The slogan was &ldquo;We demand the dignity and recognition of the contribution of rural women who are the prevalent force of agricultural production.&rdquo; &nbsp;This event facilitated by Karmajibi Nari. Change and flexibility in the role of rural women in farm production, off-farm production and&nbsp;community production are only to ensure the family&#39;s access to food and household resources.&nbsp;However, continuity and rigidity of social norms dictate that rural women and girls should assume&nbsp;home production responsibilities in rural households. The intra-household decisions on allocation&nbsp;of labour are often biased against rural women and girls.&nbsp;Other than that rally/processions, Human Chain, sports, cultural events, issue based discussion, special&nbsp;courtyard meetings were also organized by Partners. Local administration, service delivery Institutions,&nbsp;Union Parishad leaders, project beneficiaries attended the events and out of 1505 participants 933 (62%)&nbsp;were female.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Few highlights: &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n<strong>Cycle rally:&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>A colourful cycle rally was organized in association with Hemonto Cyclist group, it was held in 2nd December, 2017 at 300 feet road. Around 150 cyclists participated in the rally. They took oath to&nbsp;prevent and protest VAWG incidences everywhere and will disseminate the VAWG related messages all&nbsp;over the country. &nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Seminar on:&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>Women with disabilities and hindrance to ensure justice and VAW situation organized&nbsp;jointly by MJF and National Women Disability Association on 17th&nbsp;&nbsp;December, 2018. A key note paper&nbsp;focused on justice system and problems are facing by women with disabilities. More than 350 person with disabilities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Live Radio conference:&nbsp;</strong>Were conducted in 1st&nbsp;week of March, 2018. There are five dialogue with radio Shadhin on different role and responsibilities of women and men at family &nbsp;-society,&nbsp;importance of gender equality, gender based violence against women &amp; girls, role of state and&nbsp;discriminatory laws.&nbsp;</p>', '<h3><strong>Annual report &nbsp;<br />\r\nCampaign &ldquo;Equality through Dignity&rdquo;&nbsp;<br />\r\nReporting period: July 2017-June 2018&nbsp;</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Introduction:&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\nThe overarching goal of the &ldquo;Equality through Dignity&rdquo; campaign is to enhance women&rsquo;s private and public&nbsp;status through shifting societal mind-sets and attitude towards women to a positive perception about&nbsp;&nbsp;them to ultimately reduce discrimination and violence against women. The hypothesis is if women are&nbsp;&nbsp;respected and honoured then there will be less violence against them. To do this, the major focus is on&nbsp;&nbsp;raising mass awareness regarding the largely invisible contribution of women&rsquo;s paid and unpaid care work&nbsp;to the family, society and &nbsp;state, and to see this reflected not only in changing social norms, but in policy&nbsp;&nbsp;such as in the procedures for estimating national GDP. &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Simultaneously, the campaign aims to highlig work has on domestic violence, poverty and seeks to reshape social expectations and nor of unpaid care work within the household. The &quot;World Rural Women&#39;s Day&quot; is being observed to highlight the role played by rural women&nbsp;in food production and food security by &nbsp;7 MJF-Partners at 8 unions under Shatkhira, Jhinaidha,Kurigram, Bandarbon, Rajshahi, Shirajgonj and Manikgonj districts. Main objectives to highlight&nbsp;the &nbsp;critical role and contribution of rural women, i