(32, 'News Supplement', 'নিউজ সাপ্লিমেন্ট', '<h3><strong>12:00 AM, March 03, 2020 / LAST MODIFIED: 04:49 PM, March 03, 2020</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<h3 itemprop=\"headline\"><strong>Equality through DIGNITY</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Manusher Jonno Foundation, a non-governmental and non-profit organisation, has been running a nationwide campaign, Equality through Dignity, since 2012, to raise the status of women and reduce discrimination and violence against them. The campaign aims to change the existing and generalised negative perception of women by highlighting their contribution to the family, community, and state. Based on this understanding, on Thursday, 19 February, 2020, the Finance Minister, AHM Mustafa Kamal, affirmed in a dialogue, &lsquo;Formal Recognition of Women&rsquo;s Unaccounted Contribution,&rsquo; and that he will make a reference in his budget speech about women&rsquo;s unaccounted work and the importance of recognising it. He also said we should put our heads together to find out how this can be done.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">And hence, based on this positive note, and in anticipation of the upcoming International Women&#39;s Day, we spoke to&nbsp;<strong>Shaheen Anam, executive director, Manusher Jonno Foundation</strong>&nbsp;to learn more about equality, reduction of domestic violence, inclusion of unpaid labour into the GDP, feminism and its future prospects.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https://www.thedailystar.net/city/art-camp-equality-thru-dignity-held-ctg-1544611\">https://www.thedailystar.net/city/art-camp-equality-thru-dignity-held-ctg-1544611</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https://www.thedailystar.net/round-tables/news/recognition-womens-unaccounted-work-1665535\">https://www.thedailystar.net/round-tables/news/recognition-womens-unaccounted-work-1665535</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https://www.thedailystar.net/round-tables/gender-equality-and-women-empowerment-5628\">https://www.thedailystar.net/round-tables/gender-equality-and-women-empowerment-5628</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https://www.thedailystar.net/lifestyle/cover-story/news/equality-through-dignity-1875391\">https://www.thedailystar.net/lifestyle/cover-story/news/equality-through-dignity-1875391</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https://www.thedailystar.net/highlighting-womens-contribution-to-raise-their-status-in-society-43712\">https://www.thedailystar.net/highlighting-womens-contribution-to-raise-their-status-in-society-43712</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https://www.kalerkantho.com/online/national/2017/03/20/476816\">https://www.kalerkantho.com/online/national/2017/03/20/476816</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https://www.kalerkantho.com/print-edition/news/2019/12/12/849962\">https://www.kalerkantho.com/print-edition/news/2019/12/12/849962</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https://www.banglanews24.com/national/news/bd/561811.details\">https://www.banglanews24.com/national/news/bd/561811.details</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https://www.prothomalo.com/life/%E0%A6%AE%E0%A6%B0%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%AF%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%A6%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%AF%E0%A6%BC-%E0%A6%97%E0%A6%A1%E0%A6%BC%E0%A6%BF-%E0%A6%B8%E0%A6%AE%E0%A6%A4%E0%A6%BE\">https://www.prothomalo.com/life/%E0%A6%AE%E0%A6%B0%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%AF%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%A6%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%AF%E0%A6%BC-%E0%A6%97%E0%A6%A1%E0%A6%BC%E0%A6%BF-%E0%A6%B8%E0%A6%AE%E0%A6%A4%E0%A6%BE</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<h3><strong>12:00 AM, March 03, 2020 / LAST MODIFIED: 04:49 PM, March 03, 2020</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<h3 itemprop=\"headline\"><strong>Equality through DIGNITY</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Manusher Jonno Foundation, a non-governmental and non-profit organisation, has been running a nationwide campaign, Equality through Dignity, since 2012, to raise the status of women and reduce discrimination and violence against them. The campaign aims to change the existing and generalised negative perception of women by highlighting their contribution to the family, community, and state. Based on this understanding, on Thursday, 19 February, 2020, the Finance Minister, AHM Mustafa Kamal, affirmed in a dialogue, &lsquo;Formal Recognition of Women&rsquo;s Unaccounted Contribution,&rsquo; and that he will make a reference in his budget speech about women&rsquo;s unaccounted work and the importance of recognising it. He also said we should put our heads together to find out how this can be done.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">And hence, based on this positive note, and in anticipation of the upcoming International Women&#39;s Day, we spoke to&nbsp;<strong>Shaheen Anam, executive director, Manusher Jonno Foundation</strong>&nbsp;to learn more about equality, reduction of domestic violence, inclusion of unpaid labour into the GDP, feminism and its future prospects.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https://www.thedailystar.net/city/art-camp-equality-thru-dignity-held-ctg-1544611\">https://www.thedailystar.net/city/art-camp-equality-thru-dignity-held-ctg-1544611</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https://www.thedailystar.net/round-tables/news/recognition-womens-unaccounted-work-1665535\">https://www.thedailystar.net/round-tables/news/recognition-womens-unaccounted-work-1665535</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https://www.thedailystar.net/round-tables/gender-equality-and-women-empowerment-5628\">https://www.thedailystar.net/round-tables/gender-equality-and-women-empowerment-5628</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https://www.thedailystar.net/lifestyle/cover-story/news/equality-through-dignity-1875391\">https://www.thedailystar.net/lifestyle/cover-story/news/equality-through-dignity-1875391</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https://www.thedailystar.net/highlighting-womens-contribution-to-raise-their-status-in-society-43712\">https://www.thedailystar.net/highlighting-womens-contribution-to-raise-their-status-in-society-43712</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https://www.kalerkantho.com/online/national/2017/03/20/476816\">https://www.kalerkantho.com/online/national/2017/03/20/476816</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https://www.kalerkantho.com/print-edition/news/2019/12/12/849962\">https://www.kalerkantho.com/print-edition/news/2019/12/12/849962</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https://www.banglanews24.com/national/news/bd/561811.details\">https://www.banglanews24.com/national/news/bd/561811.details</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https://www.prothomalo.com/life/%E0%A6%AE%E0%A6%B0%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%AF%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%A6%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%AF%E0%A6%BC-%E0%A6%97%E0%A6%A1%E0%A6%BC%E0%A6%BF-%E0%A6%B8%E0%A6%AE%E0%A6%A4%E0%A6%BE\">https://www.prothomalo.com/life/%E0%A6%AE%E0%A6%B0%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%AF%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%A6%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%AF%E0%A6%BC-%E0%A6%97%E0%A6%A1%E0%A6%BC%E0%A6%BF-%E0%A6%B8%E0%A6%AE%E0%A6%A4%E0%A6%BE</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>', '2021-05-04', 2, '202106170355women\'s unpaid work -round table.jpeg', 1, 1, 1, NULL, '2021-05-09 04:40:18', '2021-06-29 20:18:26'),
(33, 'News Coverage', 'খবর কভারেজ', '<h3><strong>Women in the Economic Sector&nbsp;</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Women in Readymade Garments sector:&nbsp;</strong>The Country major export earning sector is reeadymade garments and woen comprise about 80% of the workforce. About 75% of th total export income comes from the garment sector where women are plyning a major role.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Women in Export generating Income:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Women are Directly involede in the production of export oriented products such as frozen fresh, leather and goods, handcrafts and the tea Industry. The key tasks in all these sectors are Primary Undertake by women.</p>', '<h3><strong>Women in the Economic Sector&nbsp;</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Women in Readymade Garments sector:&nbsp;</strong>The Country major export earning sector is reeadymade garments and woen comprise about 80% of the workforce. About 75% of th total export income comes from the garment sector where women are plyning a major role.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Women in Export generating Income:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Women are Directly involede in the production of export oriented products such as frozen fresh, leather and goods, handcrafts and the tea Industry. The key tasks in all these sectors are Primary Undertake by women.</p>', '2021-05-04', 2, '202106170402news clip.jpeg', 1, 1, 1, NULL, '2021-05-09 04:41:10', '2021-06-29 20:20:16'),
